                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hail the NPCs until they tell you to go talk to somebody else.  If Vual hasn't told you to talk to Henai yet, you should still be talking to Vual.    However, the basic rule still applies... every other win you can get more information.  If an NPC says you need to adventure more, go do another adventure and come back.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  (You can stockpile adventures without talking to NPCs, in that case just be sure to keep hailing the NPC until you're told you need to adventure more).
<br />

<br />
In your case, if you stopped talking to Vual when your stone gained in power (would be for tenth win) you probably need to hail him twice more at which point he should tell you to talk to Henai.  You should then be able to talk to Henai for about 4 hails.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://mywpages.comcast.net/chascraw4d/images/maesig.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
